---
title: "Primitive Types"
---



::: {.cell}

```{.python .cell-code}
type(42)
#> <class 'int'>
type(4.2)              
#> <class 'float'>
type('forty-two')      
#> <class 'str'>
type(True)             
#> <class 'bool'>
```
:::


### Type Conversion


::: {.cell}

```{.python .cell-code}
int(2.8)
#> 2
float(1)
#> 1.0
str(3)
#> '3'
bool(0)
#> False
```
:::


These considered **"Falsy"**

```python
""
0
None
```


::: {.cell}

```{.python .cell-code}
bool(0)
#> False
bool(1)
#> True
bool("")
#> False
bool("F")
#> True
bool(None)
#> False
```
:::
